Patrick and Marianne Charles were without heating during a blackout last November . 
  Couple sat down in their conservatory with a glass of wine and fired up the barbecue . 
  The conservatory quickly filled with smoke and within minutes the couple were unconscious after choking on the fumes . 
  They laid dead for 16 days before their son found them in Eastbourne . 
  Inquest heard they died of carbon monoxide poisoning . 
 